        <strong>Multi-user model:</strong> Entra ID SSO inherently supports multiple concurrent users. Each user authenticates
        with their own credentials, receives their own session token, and has their own saved layouts. All users see the same
        underlying data (read-only from SharePoint sync) and have identical permissions. User management is handled within
        Entra ID &mdash; Cloud9 controls who has access by managing their Entra directory, not within the application.
        &ldquo;Single persona&rdquo; means one permission level (viewer), not one user. Multi-persona access (Business Owner,
        Architect, Developer, Admin roles with differentiated views) is scoped for MLP.
      </p>
    </blockquote>

